<DOC><DOCNO> AP890810-0074 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-08-10-89 1228EDT</FILEID><FIRST>u i PM-Salvador     08-10 0196</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Salvador,0202</SECOND><HEAD>Rebels Attack Post in Salvadoran Capital</HEAD><DATELINE>SAN SALVADOR, El Salvador (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   Leftist rebels today plowedthrough a sentry position with a dump truck and attacked an armypost in the capital with grenades and automatic weapons,authorities and witnesses said.   Sgt. Arturo Melendez, who was commanding the Mejicanos post whenthe rebels attacked at dawn, said one soldier and one civilian werewounded.   Another guerrilla squad ambushed a truck carrying National Guardmembers to reinforce the Mejicanos post, killing one trooper andwouding two, authorities said.   Melendez told journalists about 30 insurgents firedrocket-propelled grenades at the post in northern San Salvador andsprayed it with automatic weapons fire.   The attack began when several guerrillas aboard a dump trucksmashed through a roadblock serving as the post's perimeter. Therebels also fired a grenades at the Mejicanos Town Hall, destroyingits door.   Leftist rebels are waging a nearly 10-year-old revolutionagainst a series of U.S.-backed governments. The war has killed anestimated 70,000 people, most of them civilians.   At the weekend peace conference of Central American leaders inHonduras, the five presidents signed an accord calling for peacetalks in El Salvador.</TEXT></DOC>